events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball and Terry Rozier each scored 17 points and the Charlotte Hornets came back to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 106-103 on Monday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets defeat Pelicans 106-103 for 5th straight victory

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — LeBron James broke them all out — the fadeaway jumper, the fly-through-the-lane shot, some signature dunks, one over former teammate and friend Kevin Love, the patented pregame chalk toss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Home cookin': LeBron leads Lakers over Cavs in Ohio return

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Brandon Williams scored 23 points and Ben McLemore added 21 as the patchwork Portland Trail Blazers ended a four-game losing streak with a 119-115 win over the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, McLemore lead short-handed Blazers past Pistons

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey told teammate Joel Embiid he’d step up in his absence. Then, Maxey took over the game and the fans’ chants normally reserved for the 76ers' star center.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey scores 28 as 76ers, without Harden, Embiid, beat Heat

headlines.description: — Already without Kyrie Irving and Ben Simmons, the Brooklyn Nets were down another starter to illness and lost one to injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant has 37, Nets beat Jazz 114-106 to extend good stretch

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan and Zach LaVine each scored 26 points and Nikola Vucevic had 19 points and 13 rebounds as the Chicago Bulls beat the Toronto Raptors 113-99 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine propel Bulls to 113-99 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Late in a difficult season, Christian Wood gave the Houston Rockets a reason to smile Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wood makes career-best 8 3s as Rockets down Wizards 115-97

events.name: Boston Celtics at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 36 points and the Boston Celtics beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 132-123 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 36, Celtics roll past Oklahoma City 132-123

headlines.description: — A 15-minute rain delay in an arena before the game, another interruption during a tedious and wild finish for teams jockeying for playoff position in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bullock, Mavs hold on after delay, beat Timberwolves 110-108
